1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,540
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,540 --> 00:00:03,270
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,340 --> 00:00:05,140
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:07,710
You can't do this to me.

5
00:00:08,510 --> 00:00:10,680
I have dirt on you, sir,

6
00:00:11,620 --> 00:00:13,420
and I'm not afraid
to expose everything.

7
00:00:16,190 --> 00:00:18,820
You think a threat like that
is enough to scare me?

8
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:21,060
Just to take me down,

9
00:00:21,790 --> 00:00:24,930
you'd ruin your own life too,
Ms. Choi?

10
00:00:26,430 --> 00:00:29,500
You don't have the guts to do that.

11
00:00:33,370 --> 00:00:37,140
Stop bluffing
and just hand over the recording.

12
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:41,010
Before the police issue a warrant
for your arrest,

13
00:00:42,550 --> 00:00:45,250
you have until tonight to decide.

14
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:48,550
Got it? Unbelievable.

15
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:08,640
How could Ms. Choi do such a thing?

16
00:01:09,370 --> 00:01:11,010
Her greed got the best of her.

17
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:13,280
Oh Jung Ran is just as bad.

18
00:01:13,550 --> 00:01:16,480
She's so set on hating Chloe,
she doesn't care how her son feels.

19
00:01:16,610 --> 00:01:18,380
Mr. Song must've been
pretty desperate...

20
00:01:18,380 --> 00:01:19,980
if he came to tell you himself.

21
00:01:20,390 --> 00:01:24,290
Her ambition is more important
than her son's happiness.

22
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,960
Have you heard from Mrs. Han?

23
00:01:28,830 --> 00:01:31,900
Not yet, but you asked her
to dig pretty far into the past.

24
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:34,600
It'll take some time
since she has to track down people...

25
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:36,030
who know about the past.

26
00:01:40,540 --> 00:01:41,570
What can I help you with?

27
00:01:42,210 --> 00:01:44,940
Some mail arrived for you, ma'am.

28
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:48,010
It's from Mrs. Han at Ihwachae.

29
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,610
Mrs. Han from Ihwachae?

30
00:01:54,020 --> 00:01:56,520
Then, I'll let you get to it.

31
00:02:04,530 --> 00:02:07,470
About Butler Ok...

32
00:02:08,470 --> 00:02:10,070
Take a look at this.

33
00:02:11,170 --> 00:02:12,170
What is it?

34
00:02:12,470 --> 00:02:14,070
Is there anything else
about Oh Jung Ran's past?

35
00:02:28,650 --> 00:02:31,060
Are you happy now that you've ruined
our Hyun Jun's love life?

36
00:02:33,190 --> 00:02:35,130
It's not his life that's ruined,
it's mine.

37
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:39,130
Ms. Choi failed miserably,
so Chloe ended up winning.

38
00:02:39,730 --> 00:02:40,730
Really?

39
00:02:41,830 --> 00:02:43,330
I knew I could count
on President Kim.

40
00:02:43,770 --> 00:02:44,770
President Kim?

41
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:46,700
Are you talking about Kim Myung Hui?

42
00:02:48,070 --> 00:02:49,070
Don't tell me...

43
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:51,340
Tell you what?

44
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:56,410
I just figured Chloe won
since President Kim was on her side.

45
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:57,980
That's all I meant.

46
00:02:57,980 --> 00:02:59,620
Kim Myung Hui? Give me a break.

47
00:03:00,550 --> 00:03:04,360
I lost because Ms. Choi
was hauled off by the police.

48
00:03:04,890 --> 00:03:05,890
The police?

49
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:09,760
Then Chloe must've won outright.

50
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:12,400
Does this mean
our Hyun Jun can get married?

51
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:17,440
Since it's come to this,
just let Hyun Jun follow his heart.

52
00:03:17,570 --> 00:03:18,570
Love?

53
00:03:20,710 --> 00:03:22,170
We'll see about that.

54
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:26,380
I doubt he'll keep
letting her control him.

55
00:03:26,580 --> 00:03:27,780
What do you mean by that?

56
00:03:28,710 --> 00:03:30,580
Is that a yes or a no?

57
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:35,590
It means whether I approve or not
is none of your business.

58
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:37,860
My gosh.

59
00:03:49,570 --> 00:03:50,900
You must be pretty nervous...

60
00:03:51,540 --> 00:03:53,300
if you're following me
around everywhere.

61
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:56,310
Too bad.

62
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:59,080
I have no intention
of calling off this wedding.

63
00:03:59,310 --> 00:04:01,250
You seem to be the one who's antsy.

64
00:04:04,580 --> 00:04:08,650
I know no matter what I say,
you'll insist it was her choice.

65
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:13,260
But if this isn't what Jin Ju wants,
don't you dare force her.

66
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:16,760
If you really...

67
00:04:18,430 --> 00:04:19,700
love Jin Ju,

68
00:04:21,030 --> 00:04:22,870
you won't cross that line.

69
00:04:39,020 --> 00:04:40,180
Absolutely not.

70
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:45,820
This can't be happening.

71
00:05:11,050 --> 00:05:15,690
The police will request a warrant
on charges of evidence tampering.

72
00:05:17,190 --> 00:05:18,560
The chairman said...

73
00:05:18,690 --> 00:05:22,390
that you're out of time to hesitate.

74
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:37,280
Tell him if I give the recording,
he has to settle this cleanly.

75
00:05:37,910 --> 00:05:41,080
If he breaks that promise,
I won't go down quietly.

76
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:44,320
I need to hear
the chairman's answer first...

77
00:05:47,390 --> 00:05:48,990
before I hand over the recording.

78
00:06:09,210 --> 00:06:10,210
What's this?

79
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:12,880
I was worried...

80
00:06:13,180 --> 00:06:15,550
I might've grabbed you
too hard yesterday.

81
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:21,120
You always say you're sore
and keep massaging your limbs.

82
00:06:21,290 --> 00:06:24,720
They say it's good for your joints,
so make sure you take it.

83
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:29,930
Be proactive with your joint health,
and take it consistently.

84
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:34,330
That's our Hyun Jun for you,
always so thoughtful.

85
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:40,810
And with Parents' Day coming up,
a practical gift like this is great.

86
00:06:40,940 --> 00:06:42,440
It's a nice olive branch too.

87
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:45,640
Killing two birds with one stone.
Smart thinking.

88
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:49,680
Isn't this a bribe to get me
to approve your marriage?

89
00:06:50,150 --> 00:06:52,820
Bribe or gift.
Does it matter what you call it?

90
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:56,820
What's important is that
I'm looking out for you, Ms. Oh.

91
00:06:57,090 --> 00:07:00,930
He's right.
I hear everyone's taking this now.

92
00:07:01,060 --> 00:07:02,430
Come on, hurry up and have some.

93
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:04,500
There you go.

94
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:10,030
And then give them your blessing.

95
00:07:13,740 --> 00:07:16,670
That little vixen Chloe.

96
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:18,180
Are you sure you won't let her
walk all over you?

97
00:07:19,180 --> 00:07:22,450
Marriage isn't a competition
where someone wins or loses.

98
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:23,880
Don't worry.

99
00:07:24,820 --> 00:07:26,580
I have no intention of losing.

100
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:28,620
I'm going to take everything.

101
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:33,990
Then bring me everything you have
on this Chloe.

102
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:35,990
I already know she's insolent.

103
00:07:35,990 --> 00:07:37,330
Family, education, and net worth.

104
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:38,960
Let's see whether her background...

105
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,530
will help or hurt her
in the succession war.

106
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,300
I'll run the numbers
and then I'll decide.

107
00:07:56,110 --> 00:07:57,520
Yu Na, my dear.

108
00:07:58,550 --> 00:08:00,720
What in the world is this?

109
00:08:01,020 --> 00:08:04,690
What foolish stunt did you pull
to end up in here?

110
00:08:04,990 --> 00:08:08,660
We were so shocked.
Your father's too stunned to move.

111
00:08:09,690 --> 00:08:12,200
I don't even know how I got here.

112
00:08:12,730 --> 00:08:14,870
I've been worried sick.

113
00:08:16,270 --> 00:08:19,240
Don't worry.
I'll be out of here soon.

114
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:23,170
What? How?
Do you have a plan or something?

115
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:25,080
Mom.

116
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:31,420
There's a small potted plant
on the desk in my room.

117
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:34,290
Take it to Chairman Park Tae Ho.

118
00:08:34,950 --> 00:08:37,560
If you tell him I sent you,
he'll have me released immediately.

119
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:39,660
What? A potted plant?

120
00:08:40,690 --> 00:08:42,730
What would Chairman Park want
with a potted plant?

121
00:08:43,260 --> 00:08:44,460
Just do it, please.

122
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,570
Stop asking questions
and just do it.

123
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:49,100
For crying out loud.

124
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:53,740
All right, fine. I'll do it.

125
00:08:56,270 --> 00:08:57,410
I'll be back.

126
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,110
I can't believe you.

127
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:12,320
I can't accomplish anything
trapped in here.

128
00:09:15,190 --> 00:09:16,690
I have to get out of here somehow...

129
00:09:18,260 --> 00:09:20,030
and find another way.

130
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:31,810
My daughter Yu Na said
that if I gave this to you...

131
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:34,010
you'd get her out.

132
00:09:36,150 --> 00:09:40,180
Tell Ms. Choi I've received it.

133
00:09:40,620 --> 00:09:44,590
Does this mean
you'll get my Yu Na out?

134
00:09:47,390 --> 00:09:48,390
What?

135
00:09:49,190 --> 00:09:51,000
You may leave now.

136
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,760
The chairman will look into it
and handle the matter.

137
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,430
Yes, of course.

138
00:09:57,130 --> 00:10:01,140
You must get my Yu Na out.
Please? You must.

139
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:02,970
I'll be going then.

140
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:10,650
Hey.

141
00:10:11,050 --> 00:10:12,050
Yes, sir.

142
00:10:22,690 --> 00:10:23,690
What's that?

143
00:10:30,770 --> 00:10:32,740
Check whether it's been copied.

144
00:10:33,670 --> 00:10:34,670
Yes, sir.

145
00:10:46,650 --> 00:10:47,650
Well...

146
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:49,550
What brings you to my study?

147
00:10:50,590 --> 00:10:52,720
I thought I'd help you
get ready for work.

148
00:10:57,930 --> 00:11:00,800
You must be upset over what happened
with Ms. Choi this morning.

149
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,970
About Min Jun's marriage...

150
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:07,840
Can I assume that deal is
off the table?

151
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:14,550
Did you offer your help today
in the hope that I'd confirm it?

152
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:19,250
I wanted to hear the answer
from you personally, sir.

153
00:11:24,090 --> 00:11:25,360
You have nothing to worry about.

154
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:29,530
I'm going to take care
of Ms. Choi for good.

155
00:11:30,260 --> 00:11:31,330
That's a relief.

156
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:34,570
I was so worried
about Min Jun's marriage.

157
00:11:35,030 --> 00:11:37,500
The bond between a couple
is no small thing, after all.

158
00:11:38,770 --> 00:11:39,840
I suppose so.

159
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:49,050
What was
your first marriage like, sir?

160
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,150
My first marriage?

161
00:11:54,290 --> 00:11:56,420
All this talk about marriage...

162
00:11:56,490 --> 00:12:00,260
made me wonder
what it was like for you with her.

163
00:12:01,060 --> 00:12:03,590
I seem to recall hearing
she was very ill.

164
00:12:05,630 --> 00:12:08,000
She suffered from a heart condition.

165
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,530
After her father died, the shock...

166
00:12:11,340 --> 00:12:14,540
made her illness much worse,
and she left us. But...

167
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:21,510
But why are you suddenly
bringing all this up?

168
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:26,550
I just got curious.
There's no other reason.

169
00:12:29,420 --> 00:12:30,420
Is that so?

170
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:34,760
You should get to work.
Manager Kang must be waiting.

171
00:12:48,470 --> 00:12:51,880
Are these the documents
I've been looking for...

172
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:56,580
about Oh Jung Ran's past
and her evil deeds?

173
00:12:57,380 --> 00:12:58,420
That's correct.

174
00:13:05,890 --> 00:13:07,260
(Bion Tech)

175
00:13:10,490 --> 00:13:11,730
(Death Certificate: Moon Jeong Hye)

176
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:13,430
(Ventricular tachycardia,
Mioxin poisoning, Mioxin overdose)

177
00:13:15,370 --> 00:13:16,930
(Death Certificate
(Coroner's Report))

178
00:13:18,470 --> 00:13:21,210
Chairman Park Tae Ho's first wife,

179
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:23,170
the daughter
of Munhwadang's chairman,

180
00:13:23,170 --> 00:13:26,540
had a long-standing heart condition
before she passed away.

181
00:13:26,540 --> 00:13:28,110
Oh Jung Ran...

182
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:31,750
was her caregiver.

183
00:13:32,550 --> 00:13:37,050
There are rumors that Ms. Oh
was involved in her death.

184
00:13:37,420 --> 00:13:38,720
If you don't believe me,

185
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:41,730
feel free to confirm it
for yourself.

186
00:13:42,730 --> 00:13:44,900
I confirmed it with Chairman Park...

187
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:47,100
regarding
the Munhwadang chairman's daughter.

188
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:50,330
As for whether Oh Jung Ran
really killed her,

189
00:13:51,140 --> 00:13:53,140
and the secret she's hiding?

190
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:55,440
I'll find out for myself.

191
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:04,080
Tell me.

192
00:14:06,780 --> 00:14:09,790
Did you tell Myung Hui
about Munhwadang?

193
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:11,920
Munhwadang?

194
00:14:13,490 --> 00:14:15,460
Why would I bring up
that dreary old story?

195
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:17,730
Really?

196
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:22,300
Why?
Did Kim Myung Hui say something?

197
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,470
Never mind.

198
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:28,470
So how's the gallery business
coming along?

199
00:14:30,140 --> 00:14:32,040
I'm about to start looking into it.

200
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:35,750
I asked you to do that ages ago,
and you're just getting to it now?

201
00:14:35,810 --> 00:14:37,780
I've been busy with a few things.

202
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:41,750
Yes, busy sticking your nose
where it doesn't belong.

203
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:44,320
First that con artist,
and now Ms. Choi.

204
00:14:44,620 --> 00:14:45,790
You think I wouldn't know?

205
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:47,590
I told you, it's all taken care of.

206
00:14:48,490 --> 00:14:51,460
Although, there's still the matter
of Hyun Jun's wedding.

207
00:14:51,530 --> 00:14:54,630
The deadline we gave
Assemblyman Kwon is coming up.

208
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:57,100
Just go do what you were told.

209
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:58,270
Fine.

210
00:14:59,140 --> 00:15:00,740
You're such a nag.

211
00:15:02,410 --> 00:15:03,440
Unbelievable.

212
00:15:03,610 --> 00:15:07,340
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

213
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:12,120
Right.

214
00:15:13,650 --> 00:15:15,020
We checked the flash drive,

215
00:15:15,020 --> 00:15:18,090
and there was no sign
the audio evidence had been copied.

216
00:15:20,620 --> 00:15:21,630
Good.

217
00:15:23,730 --> 00:15:25,000
And now...

218
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:42,050
What took you so long?

219
00:15:42,050 --> 00:15:44,420
You should've come here right away
after getting the recording.

220
00:15:44,920 --> 00:15:47,650
I had to make sure
you didn't make a copy.

221
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:50,690
There aren't any.

222
00:15:52,790 --> 00:15:55,530
A piece of work like you
didn't even make a copy?

223
00:15:56,090 --> 00:15:57,090
That's right.

224
00:15:57,360 --> 00:16:00,100
I didn't think I'd actually have
to hand over the original.

225
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:03,830
Besides, it'd be a disaster
if a copy I made got leaked.

226
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:09,570
And since I've been stuck in here,
I've had no time to make one.

227
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:14,350
So, I can leave now, right?

228
00:16:14,450 --> 00:16:15,610
About that...

229
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:19,820
That's up to the police to decide.

230
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:23,290
What are you doing?

231
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:26,160
This isn't what we agreed on.

232
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:32,500
I just can't believe you
when you say you don't have a copy.

233
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,740
You can check the recorder log.

234
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:40,140
I'm sure you've checked already.

235
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:42,910
Still, I can't trust you.

236
00:16:50,680 --> 00:16:51,780
Don't tell me...

237
00:16:52,180 --> 00:16:54,420
Was this your plan from the start?

238
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:57,760
Did you lock me up in here
so you could get the recording?

239
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:00,820
Was it you...

240
00:17:01,090 --> 00:17:03,760
who sabotaged the equipment
and planted my fingerprints?

241
00:17:08,430 --> 00:17:09,430
Choi Yu Na.

242
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,440
You're so naive.

243
00:17:15,870 --> 00:17:19,410
You can only see
what's right in front of you.

244
00:17:20,410 --> 00:17:23,510
Because you're always
so shortsighted,

245
00:17:23,780 --> 00:17:25,350
you're in this mess.

246
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:28,050
Sir!

247
00:17:32,690 --> 00:17:35,130
Did you really think
you could take on Park Tae Ho,

248
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:38,130
find my weakness, use it against me,

249
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:41,030
and get away with it?

250
00:17:43,570 --> 00:17:47,300
The marriage you dreamed of,
your career, your future...

251
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:49,840
I gave it all to you.

252
00:17:51,540 --> 00:17:55,050
But you were ungrateful
and pushed too far,

253
00:17:55,910 --> 00:17:58,020
so it's only right
that I take everything back.

254
00:18:02,190 --> 00:18:03,720
You'll regret this.

255
00:18:05,590 --> 00:18:08,130
I'm going to make you
regret using me...

256
00:18:09,460 --> 00:18:11,130
and throwing me away!

257
00:18:15,630 --> 00:18:17,530
Fine. Go ahead and try.

258
00:18:18,570 --> 00:18:20,740
If you manage to make me regret it,

259
00:18:22,070 --> 00:18:24,680
I'll bow my head
and admit I was wrong.

260
00:18:42,290 --> 00:18:44,190
Chloe was right.

261
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:54,200
My mom should've
delivered it by now.

262
00:18:55,570 --> 00:18:57,270
So why haven't I heard anything?

263
00:19:03,850 --> 00:19:04,980
Excuse me.

264
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:16,030
Could they have a moment, please?

265
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:26,100
What is this?

266
00:19:26,940 --> 00:19:29,170
Did you come here to gloat?

267
00:19:29,610 --> 00:19:33,940
Maybe to gloat a little,
and maybe to get you out.

268
00:19:34,980 --> 00:19:35,980
Get me out?

269
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:43,490
Forget it. The chairman will deal
with this soon.

270
00:19:44,450 --> 00:19:47,960
Don't tell me you gave up
your leverage over Chairman Park...

271
00:19:48,260 --> 00:19:50,190
and begged him
to get you out of here.

272
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:58,640
It was just a transaction,
a mutual exchange.

273
00:19:58,800 --> 00:19:59,940
A transaction?

274
00:20:03,170 --> 00:20:06,540
You still don't know
you were framed, do you?

275
00:20:07,780 --> 00:20:08,910
What do you mean I was set up?

276
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:12,250
You think Chairman Park
will get you out of here?

277
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:16,590
He's the one who put you in here
in the first place.

278
00:20:17,150 --> 00:20:18,160
What?

279
00:20:20,590 --> 00:20:22,430
What are you talking about?

280
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:26,130
You said you didn't use the computer
in the lab.

281
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:31,170
Then how did your fingerprints
end up on it?

282
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:35,040
It can't be.

283
00:20:36,070 --> 00:20:39,440
Chairman Park set you up
to get his hands on that recording.

284
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:42,480
The only person
who can get you out of this now...

285
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:45,120
is me.

286
00:20:57,490 --> 00:20:59,900
Do you believe me now?

287
00:21:02,170 --> 00:21:03,400
Park Tae Ho...

288
00:21:04,370 --> 00:21:06,240
I thought he'd at least
keep his word.

289
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:10,710
He used me and cast me aside
from the very beginning.

290
00:21:13,710 --> 00:21:15,710
I'm going to make him pay.

291
00:21:20,120 --> 00:21:21,120
You.

292
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:23,620
Can you really get me out of here?

293
00:21:24,450 --> 00:21:26,520
Are you trying to trick me
like Park Tae Ho did?

294
00:21:27,360 --> 00:21:31,190
I'm the witness
who can prove your innocence.

295
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:34,530
How can you do that?

296
00:21:35,330 --> 00:21:39,270
The police estimate
the incident happened around 6 p.m.

297
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:43,040
They claim the equipment failed
right after you left,

298
00:21:44,140 --> 00:21:45,240
but they're wrong.

299
00:21:45,910 --> 00:21:48,010
Because I went to the system room...

300
00:21:48,010 --> 00:21:49,910
after the supposed time
of the incident.

301
00:21:51,620 --> 00:21:54,820
My testimony will change
the official timeline.

302
00:21:55,550 --> 00:21:57,820
Even though
Chairman Park pulled strings,

303
00:21:57,820 --> 00:22:00,060
it'll be much harder for them
to pin this on you...

304
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:02,460
now that a new witness has appeared.

305
00:22:03,190 --> 00:22:06,830
You might still be questioned,
but they should release you for now.

306
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:08,370
Are you sure?

307
00:22:09,430 --> 00:22:12,240
Then get me out of here right now.

308
00:22:14,670 --> 00:22:15,810
And if I do?

309
00:22:16,610 --> 00:22:19,110
What's in it for me?

310
00:22:20,510 --> 00:22:21,510
What?

311
00:22:21,780 --> 00:22:24,920
You already gave Chairman Park
the dirt you had on him.

312
00:22:26,020 --> 00:22:28,720
Doesn't that mean our deal is over?

313
00:22:29,620 --> 00:22:31,960
I have no reason to help you.

314
00:22:32,020 --> 00:22:34,190
Then we can make another deal.

315
00:22:34,730 --> 00:22:38,630
If you help me,
I'll do anything you want.

316
00:22:44,530 --> 00:22:45,540
Anything...

317
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:48,170
I want?

318
00:22:51,910 --> 00:22:55,510
Then kneel down and beg me.

319
00:22:57,110 --> 00:22:58,420
Show me...

320
00:22:58,980 --> 00:23:01,320
if you'd really do...

321
00:23:02,750 --> 00:23:03,850
anything I want.

322
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:49,370
I have to endure this.

323
00:23:52,840 --> 00:23:55,510
If I want to get out of here
and have another chance,

324
00:23:57,140 --> 00:23:59,610
I can put up
with this kind of humiliation.

325
00:24:02,850 --> 00:24:03,950
Choi Yu Na.

326
00:24:06,450 --> 00:24:10,050
At last, you're on your knees,
begging me.

327
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:14,660
But this is just the beginning.

328
00:24:16,730 --> 00:24:17,730
All right.

329
00:24:18,430 --> 00:24:19,430
Let's...

330
00:24:24,270 --> 00:24:25,470
work together again.

331
00:24:30,010 --> 00:24:31,470
I'll drag you back to that moment...

332
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:34,310
- from seven years ago.
- Yu Na, you have to help me!

333
00:24:35,050 --> 00:24:36,810
- Yu Na...
- To the very moment...

334
00:24:36,810 --> 00:24:38,950
my father was wrongfully killed.

335
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:40,620
That's where I'm taking you.

336
00:24:41,150 --> 00:24:43,390
I'll make you out
to be a murderer...

337
00:24:44,150 --> 00:24:45,890
and make your life
a living nightmare.

338
00:24:57,630 --> 00:24:58,840
I'll help you.

339
00:25:23,560 --> 00:25:25,330
(Mioxin)

340
00:25:42,250 --> 00:25:44,550
What's this? Medicine?

341
00:25:46,550 --> 00:25:48,050
(Mioxin)

342
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:49,120
Mioxin?

343
00:25:51,250 --> 00:25:52,560
What's Mioxin...

344
00:25:52,690 --> 00:25:53,860
(Mioxin)

345
00:25:58,560 --> 00:25:59,560
Tell me.

346
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:02,830
Did you tell Myung Hui
about Munhwadang?

347
00:26:04,070 --> 00:26:08,440
Kim Myung Hui couldn't have,
could she?

348
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:15,650
For goodness' sake.

349
00:26:17,150 --> 00:26:18,150
Oh, dear.

350
00:26:18,550 --> 00:26:21,690
Chairman Park said
he'd get Yu Na released,

351
00:26:22,350 --> 00:26:24,250
so why haven't we heard
anything yet?

352
00:26:24,820 --> 00:26:28,390
Honestly.
My gosh. Is that you, Yu Na?

353
00:26:32,860 --> 00:26:35,530
Unbelievable. What brings you here?

354
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:40,140
What... Hold on. Min Jun?

355
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:43,410
Stop talking to him
like he's our son-in-law.

356
00:26:43,710 --> 00:26:45,610
I told you, the engagement is off.

357
00:26:46,040 --> 00:26:48,280
Why are you here
when it's over between you two?

358
00:26:48,910 --> 00:26:50,250
I'm here because...

359
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:51,720
I have questions about...

360
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:53,350
the Temi Bio incident
from seven years ago.

361
00:26:54,250 --> 00:26:56,150
What was that?

362
00:26:56,620 --> 00:26:57,620
Temi Bio?

363
00:27:03,990 --> 00:27:05,260
Kim Myung Hui, you.

364
00:27:07,460 --> 00:27:10,800
You left the medicine bottle
in the annex, didn't you?

365
00:27:12,970 --> 00:27:14,570
So you do remember.

366
00:27:16,470 --> 00:27:21,080
It's not something you'd forget,
even after 30 years.

367
00:27:22,450 --> 00:27:24,610
After all, you killed someone
with that medicine.

368
00:27:31,020 --> 00:27:33,360
CEO Baek Jun Gi
and his daughter Baek Jin Ju.

369
00:27:35,030 --> 00:27:36,130
You know them, don't you?

370
00:27:37,090 --> 00:27:39,100
CEO Baek...

371
00:27:40,460 --> 00:27:41,970
and Jin Ju?

372
00:27:42,900 --> 00:27:45,800
I heard you were practically family
for a long time.

373
00:27:46,100 --> 00:27:47,440
Around the time of the accident,

374
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:50,310
did anything seem unusual to you?

375
00:27:50,610 --> 00:27:53,480
Did CEO Baek really commit suicide?

376
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:58,080
And how was
the Temi Bio acquisition finalized?

377
00:27:58,250 --> 00:27:59,250
For goodness' sake.

378
00:28:00,550 --> 00:28:02,420
I don't know.

379
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:05,860
You were longtime friends
with the late CEO Baek.

380
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:07,590
Didn't you handle everything
after the accident,

381
00:28:07,590 --> 00:28:08,730
including the funeral?

382
00:28:09,260 --> 00:28:12,160
You even found his will
and held a press conference.

383
00:28:13,060 --> 00:28:16,670
- Where's the will? May I see it?
- Oh, dear.

384
00:28:17,170 --> 00:28:19,570
I'll take anything you know
about the incident from seven years ago,

385
00:28:20,070 --> 00:28:21,270
so please tell me.

386
00:28:22,370 --> 00:28:26,040
I'm telling you,
I don't know anything.

387
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:29,380
My, why are you shaking like this?

388
00:28:30,780 --> 00:28:33,650
- Mr. Choi.
- No, stop it. Just stop.

389
00:28:33,850 --> 00:28:36,650
I'm telling you, my only crime
was doing what I was told.

390
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:38,490
You did what you were told?

391
00:28:39,190 --> 00:28:40,790
What crime are you talking about?

392
00:28:41,790 --> 00:28:44,160
Oh, please. There was no crime.

393
00:28:44,430 --> 00:28:46,700
My husband hasn't slept in days,

394
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:48,930
and with Yu Na under arrest,

395
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:51,840
he's not thinking clearly.
He misspoke.

396
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:53,040
Let's just drop it.

397
00:28:53,170 --> 00:28:55,610
You said you were following orders.

398
00:28:55,610 --> 00:28:57,610
Who gave you the order,
and what was it?

399
00:28:58,480 --> 00:28:59,980
Please, just tell me.

400
00:29:00,410 --> 00:29:02,350
For Jin Ju's sake, please.

401
00:29:02,350 --> 00:29:03,480
Jin Ju!

402
00:29:04,710 --> 00:29:06,620
There, there. It's okay.

403
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:08,650
Stop it. I said that's enough!

404
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:11,450
Mr. Choi, who gave you the order,
and what was it?

405
00:29:11,450 --> 00:29:13,720
- What... Goodness me.
- Stop it.

406
00:29:14,590 --> 00:29:15,590
Yu Na.

407
00:29:32,380 --> 00:29:35,780
What did your father mean?
What orders was he following?

408
00:29:37,210 --> 00:29:38,620
You know something, don't you?

409
00:29:41,420 --> 00:29:43,450
I was just questioned by the police.

410
00:29:43,850 --> 00:29:46,460
I got fired, my wedding is off,

411
00:29:47,760 --> 00:29:49,430
and you're not even worried
about me?

412
00:29:49,530 --> 00:29:51,130
Just answer my question.

413
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:55,100
Why the sudden interest
in what happened seven years ago?

414
00:29:58,940 --> 00:29:59,940
Because I regret it.

415
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:02,740
Looking back,

416
00:30:03,810 --> 00:30:07,310
I regret not investigating it
more thoroughly.

417
00:30:10,180 --> 00:30:13,350
So if you know anything,
please, just tell me.

418
00:30:13,380 --> 00:30:14,680
If you're that desperate to know...

419
00:30:19,060 --> 00:30:20,890
What? Did you remember something?

420
00:30:24,460 --> 00:30:25,460
No.

421
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:27,730
How would I know what happened?

422
00:30:27,730 --> 00:30:29,070
But your father...

423
00:30:29,130 --> 00:30:30,300
My dad...

424
00:30:32,500 --> 00:30:35,970
Seeing Chloe reminded him of Jin Ju,
and it's shaken him up.

425
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:37,910
He's always been fainthearted.

426
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:43,480
That's all it is, so you can go now.

427
00:30:43,610 --> 00:30:47,020
He saw Chloe?
Are you saying she was here?

428
00:30:49,190 --> 00:30:52,460
It's always about Baek Jin Ju
or Chloe with you, isn't it?

429
00:30:55,060 --> 00:30:56,130
Forget it.

430
00:30:56,590 --> 00:30:58,660
I don't want to say another word,

431
00:31:00,030 --> 00:31:01,060
so get out.

432
00:31:18,920 --> 00:31:19,920
It's me.

433
00:31:20,850 --> 00:31:23,490
I've got something we can use
to pressure Chairman Park.

434
00:31:25,390 --> 00:31:26,620
It's the truth about...

435
00:31:26,620 --> 00:31:28,790
what happened seven years ago
that he's been hiding.

436
00:31:29,690 --> 00:31:30,990
A secret that Park Min Jun,

437
00:31:31,460 --> 00:31:33,530
of all people, must never find out.

438
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:39,700
I knew it. You did know something.

439
00:31:42,340 --> 00:31:43,340
Tell me.

440
00:31:44,210 --> 00:31:47,340
What happened seven years ago
that I'm not supposed to know about?

441
00:31:49,150 --> 00:31:50,380
Tell me right now.

442
00:32:00,060 --> 00:32:02,330
I've found out about your past.

443
00:32:04,330 --> 00:32:06,260
The past you tried to hide.

444
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:11,430
The crime of murdering the daughter
of Munhwadang's chairman.

445
00:32:12,740 --> 00:32:13,740
Now,

446
00:32:14,470 --> 00:32:16,410
you won't be able
to hide it anymore.

447
00:32:45,700 --> 00:32:48,740
(Pearl in Red)

448
00:32:48,910 --> 00:32:51,540
I don't want Chloe to marry
into the Adele family.

449
00:32:51,670 --> 00:32:53,710
I won't give up on this marriage.

450
00:32:53,710 --> 00:32:55,310
I've made my decision,

451
00:32:55,310 --> 00:32:56,710
and since
there's no reason to call it off,

452
00:32:56,710 --> 00:32:57,710
I'm moving forward with it.

453
00:32:57,710 --> 00:32:59,350
What's the point of this?

454
00:32:59,350 --> 00:33:03,190
It's my way of warning you
to stay out of my way.

455
00:33:03,190 --> 00:33:05,460
I'll make her regret this.

456
00:33:05,590 --> 00:33:08,090
I have to act
before Min Jun ruins everything.

457
00:33:08,090 --> 00:33:09,790
I'll squeeze Chairman Park...

458
00:33:09,860 --> 00:33:13,000
for everything I can get
as fast as possible.

459
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:15,600
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
